<http://www.spektrix.com/sidwilliams/event/190601ALDLJSDKCDJKDDQMDMLJQHQBQMR> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "The Heels";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">The Heels: Nashville’s Fastest Rising Country Music Queens</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">With Opening Act: Justine Lynn</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">The Heels</span>, a dynamic trio from Canada now living in Nashville and the West Coast of Canada, are making waves in the country music scene with their high-energy shows, three-part harmonies, and good-natured brash. Crowned Country Group of the Year at the Josie Music Awards, their single \"Hush Money\" hit number one in France, solidifying their status. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>They also won Group of the Year, Music Video of the Year, and Emerging Artist of the Year at the BCCMA Awards in Canada. Their album “I Am” went viral on TikTok, topping iTunes Country charts in over ten countries. Their single “Take the Trailer” is now being played nationally throughout North America on the iHeart Radio network. Since moving to Nashville in February 2024, they play 20 live shows monthly, selling out iconic venues like The Bluebird Cafe and The Listening Room. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Collaborating with Tom Jackson Productions, their live shows are a must-see. Their upcoming single, “Love, Heals,” produced by Marti Frederiksen and Desmond Child and written by Marcus and Levi Hummon (writers of Tim McGraw's \"Cowboy in Me,\" Dixie Chicks' \"Cowboy Take Me Away\") and Tom Douglas (co writer of Miranda Lambert's \"The House That Built Me\"), promises to be a standout. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Bobbi, Brittni, and Kyla blend country, pop, and spiritual sounds, creating a soul-deep genre-bending experience. Follow their journey at www.theheelsmusic.com.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">OPENING ACT JUSTINE LYNN</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">A global soul with country roots</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Justine Lynn is a Vancouver-based country artist with a powerhouse voice and a sound that has always carried more grit and soul than the genre usually allows.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>With her new single “Roses” out May 29, 2026, she takes a bold step into blues-country territory, drawing on the South African roots and jazz-infused musical foundation that have shaped her since the beginning.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Since releasing her debut EP in 2019, Justine has earned airplay on more than 35 Canadian radio stations, landed in the Top 50 on SiriusXM Canada’s Top of the Country chart, hit number two on Amazon Music’s Breakthrough Country Playlist, and opened for Dallas Smith, Meghan Patrick, and Dean Brody.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>She is also the founder of Country for a Cause, an annual fundraiser supporting wildlife conservation in South Africa through the Wild Tomorrow Fund. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Justine Lynn is an artist with something real to say, and a voice built to say it. www.justinelynn.com<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Join The Heels with Justine Lynn this September at the Sid!</span><span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-09-26T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/sidwilliams/files/855b5536-c9f2-4286-ab0a-313bf8fb70df.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/sidwilliams/location/201AGBHDRLQHNHPHKKMPKLGPMDRDTDMVL>;
  schema:organizer <https://spektrix.com/sidwilliams/organization/comox-valley-homes-team-royal-lepage>;
  schema:url <https://www.sidwilliamstheatre.com/events/the-heels/>;
  schema:offers _:8bf1a82a9b7c466fab0eeb10a30b9820954;
  schema:keywords "Live music - Country";
  schema:duration "PT300M";
  schema:endDate "2026-09-27T00:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

